title: Laura Whitmore jets home and stays in before I'm a Celebrity kicks off
text:
Laura Whitmore is set to jet off to Australia in the next few weeks, but she made sure to fit in a trip home first. The presenter will once again be fronting I'm A Celebrity... Get Me Out of Here Now with former winner Joe Swash.
Laura Over the weekend, the 30-year-old made sure to get her pizza fix at one of her favourite local spots, Pizza'n'Cream in Bray.
However, instead of hitting the town afterwards, the party girl stayed in to watch the Late Late Show.
Elsewhere, model and singer Michele McGrath and her boyfriend Cathal Pendred were delighted when their dog Ringo was found yesterday.
The Liir singer put out an appeal last week when her pooch went missing.
"We've been reunited with Ringo. Thanks to everybody who helped get him home. Unbelievable support," Cathal said.
"We are so happy to have him home," Michele added.
Meanwhile, the models that party together stay together as Thalia Heffernan and Holly Carpenter enjoyed a night out to celebrate the former Miss Ireland's 24th birthday.
Leo is man of the year Minister Leo Varadkar was named Irish Tatler Man of the Year in Dublin this weekend.
Bressie scooped the award for 'Men in the Media' and Michael O Muircheartaigh was entered into the hall of fame.
